Package edu.ncsu.csc216.app_manager.model.application

Class Application

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.app_manager.model.application.Application
public class Application extends Object
Represents an Application object in the ApplicationManager program. Each application has its own state which is updated from Commands passed to it from the UI. Other fields may be updated when a Command is passed. This class is also the context class for the AppState interface and inner State classes.
Author:
Christine Weld

  • Constructor Details

    • Application

      public Application(int appId, Application.AppType appType, String summary, String note)
      Constructs an Application object managed by the program with given fields appId, appType, summary, and note, with other fields state, summary, reviewer, processPaperwork, resolution, and notes initialized to null or false values. Adds an initial note to the notes array.
      Parameters:
      appId - int id of application
      appType - AppType type of application
      summary - String summary of application
      note - String note for application notes array
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - "Application cannot be created." if any parameters are null or empty strings, or id is invalid input: '<' 1.

    • Application

      public Application(int appId, String state, String appType, String summary, String reviewer, boolean processPaperwork, String resolution, ArrayList<String> notes)
      Constructs an Application object with given values for all fields.
      Parameters:
      appId - int id of application
      state - State state of application
      appType - AppType type of application
      summary - String summary of application
      reviewer - String reviewer for application
      processPaperwork - boolean true if paperwork processed for application
      resolution - Resolution of application
      notes - ArrayList of notes for application
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - "Application cannot be created." if any parameters are null or empty strings, or id is invalid input: '<' 1.

    • update

      public void update(Command command)
      Delegates to the current state's updateState(Command) method. Update the Application based on the given Command. An UnsupportedOperationException is thrown if the Command is not a valid action for the given state.
      Parameters:
      command - Command describing the action that will update the Application's state.
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - if the Command is not a valid action for the given state.
